Rating: 4
I grew up with European-type scones like these, but they were much heavier. These are light and cakey on the inside and golden and crunchy on the outside. Delicate and subtle in flavour. Perfect with Earl Grey tea. Ridiculously easy to make.

Rating: 4
These are delicious--but take note, as BRITISH scones, they are quite different from the American variety: less sweet (normally eaten with jam and cream), much lighter and fluffier, and it feels less oily. I definitely prefer these to the American scones, but in any case, you'd want to be aware of what you're getting. I normally add zest from two lemons, and substitute honey (added w/ liquid ingredients) for the sugar. I also make 24 mini scones, rather than one big round.

