Rating: 3
I've had this recipe since it first appeared in the magazine. It duplicates the recipe for the scones that the Dorchester Hotel in London serves for afternoon tea. These are not dry, crumbly scones but more delicate and cake-like as the recipe states. I make this in an 8" round cake pan rather than patting it into a round on a baking sheet.

